Apologies for the confusion. It seems that there was an issue with the content attribute in the `nav ul li a::after`. Please update the following CSS rule:

Change this:
```css
nav ul li a::after {
  content: ‘’;
  position: absolute;
  ...
}
```

To this:

```css
nav ul li a::after {
  content: '';
  position: absolute;
  ...
}
```

Notice that the single quotes surrounding the content attribute have been changed. Once you update this, the cool line hover effect should work as expected. Enjoy your new line hover effect on the navigation bar!
